<div class="fewWords">

<h2 class="dontend" id="toc0"> V1 of the product was way too slow.  <a href="#toc0"> <sup><i class="fa fa-link invert" ></i></sup> </a></h2>
<p>If we take the code in early Sept as v1, just after the report page was created; then the rewrites to reduce page loading time, and graph display improvements as v2; v2.3 which is released, then unreleased work since then as v3.  v1 rendered tabs in 15-30s (depending on sample duration), v2 rendered tabs in 1-5s, v3 is rendering &lt;1s for up to a day, and between 1 and 5s for longer periods. I think the top value will be smaller when the code isn't running on 30.121, as that has higher traffic dropouts.  I would like to build v4, which fixes many PHP specific issues, and should reduce execution cost by 30% for PHP sections (i.e. no impact on network or database); but this requires time from FSJ.</p>

<p>Design/UX niggles<br />
I think the following are necessary to improve our <strong>product</strong>, not focussed on code.</p>

<ul class="ulbasic">
    <li class="libasic">Speed up login page DONE, not deployed.</li>
    <li class="libasic">Ensure setups with 4-6 clocks works cleanly, mostly work on graphs (ref Francios Botha).</li>
    <li class="libasic">Do more work on burger menu placement.</li>
    <li class="libasic">Most relevant columns to machine type in tripple plot (ref SK) DONE.</li>
    <li class="libasic">Iterate the date pickers abit more.</li>
    <li class="libasic">In alerts tab, bold == sorted column (ref KID).</li>
    <li class="libasic">Ensure all the links in word documents work.</li>
    <li class="libasic">Add 20px font throughout, as requested by Sales.</li>
    <li class="libasic"><b>Add 2500px version as requested by Sales</b>.  This need a bigger screen for me.</li>
    <li class="libasic">Implement the browser bug list on my pad.</li>
    <li class="libasic">Get rid of stupid MSIE select animation.</li>
    <li class="libasic">Drop random “orgspk” from UI, unless its banking terminology. For example, add an Excel logo, rather than “CSV”.</li>
    <li class="libasic">Make work in a wider range of browsers (in progress).</li>
</ul>

<p>New Features</p>

<ul class="ulbasic">
    <li class="libasic">Add ability to reset password. DONE on CLI.</li>
    <li class="libasic">The RGH specced “logging tab” replacement.</li>
    <li class="libasic">The clocks page (ref SK, I can design if you want?).</li>
    <li class="libasic">Business process: manage authorised contact details on PDF. </li>
    <li class="libasic">Send an SNMP to Nagois, when an alert is created; for our internal viewing, so we can see all clients concurrently.</li>
    <li class="libasic">Current value in tooltip, on graphs.</li>
    <li class="libasic">Business process: mail PDFs to people once per week.</li>
    <li class="libasic">Business process: heartbeat SNMP packets.</li>
    <li class="libasic">Business process: the second ~ more detailed ~ PDF.</li>
    <li class="libasic">Improve credibility on site by linking relevant law articles.</li>
    <li class="libasic">Tidyup codebase (again) to better support internationalisation, like it states in my contract.  This option gets re-added to my workflow every few months.</li>
    <li class="libasic">Move font-size choice into the per-client config.</li>
    <li class="libasic">Create optional high contrast skin.  Also useful for printing.</li>
    <li class="libasic">It would improve the UX if different identification/authentication patterns where considered.  This is a RnD<a class="" href="https://www.google.co.uk/search?q=RnD">?</a> option mostly.  Consider a single signon thing.</li>
    <li class="libasic">Make graphs resize on browser resize.</li>
    <li class="libasic">“GUIify” create client feature.</li>
</ul>

<p>Infrastructure</p>

<ul class="ulbasic">
    <li class="libasic">Deploy SSL.</li>
    <li class="libasic">Write a HLL branded link checker (internal use only).</li>
    <li class="libasic">Create a REST login call for automation objectives.</li>
    <li class="libasic">Add more unit tests, to PHP.</li>
    <li class="libasic">Cycle DB passwords.</li>
    <li class="libasic">Manage cron scripts better &amp;&amp; their logging.</li>
    <li class="libasic">Maybe send cron errors to Nagios, so we can see a easy to read form.</li>
    <li class="libasic">Manage mongo better, see replicaSet errors in particular.</li>
    <li class="libasic">Improve CSS “add objects”, improve naming clarity.</li>
</ul>

<p>More performance improvements</p>

<ul class="ulbasic">
    <li class="libasic">Drop Apache in favour of NginX<a class="" href="https://www.google.co.uk/search?q=NginX">?</a>, as faster.</li>
    <li class="libasic">Move to HTTP2, where supported, as faster.</li>
    <li class="libasic">Move to PHP-FGM as faster on PHP specific bits, as not compiling code on each request.</li>
    <li class="libasic">Compile PHP into bytecode blob.  More performance gains (but no so much as previous).</li>
    <li class="libasic">Move sessions to mongo (probable speed improvement).</li>
</ul>


</div>
